I want to make a plugin to handle websocket on red5 server.

develop with eclipse herios.
I use these jar files as Referenced Libraries
 logback-core-0.9.18.jar
 logback-classic-0.9.18.jar
 slf4j-api-1.5.10.jar
 mina-core-2.0.0-RC1.jar
 red5.jar
 spring-context-3.0.0.jar

how to use this.
compile and make jar file with manifest.mf. (WebSocketPlugin.jar)
put this jar on red5-home/plugins/
write this on red5-home/conf/red5.xml after PluginLauncher
	<bean id="webSocketTransport" class="com.ttProject.red5.server.plugin.websocket.WebSocketTransport" init-method="start">
		<property name="port" value="8080"/>
	</bean>
run red5 on console.
connect with red5 server on that port number(8080) from WebSocket.
send some message, you can see that message on console.

I checked this with red5 0.9.1 on Mac.
and Google Chrome, Safari on Mac, Google Chrome on WinXP

Thanks
Takahiko Toda(poepoemix@hotmail.com)
